<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>float horizontal navigation bar code</title>

        <style>
            ul{
                list-style-type: none;
                overflow: hidden;
                padding: 0;
                margin: 0;
            }
            li{
                float: left;
            }
            li a {
                display: block;
                padding: 10px;
                background-color: darkcyan;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>float horizontal navigation bar code check</h1>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#home">home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#about us">about us</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact">contact</a></li>
           
        </ul>
        <p><b>Note:</b> If a !DOCTYPE is not specified, floating items can produce unexpected results.</p>
<p>A background color is added to the links to show the link area. The whole link area is clickable, not just the text.</p>
<p><b>Note:</b> overflow:hidden is added to the ul element to prevent li elements from going outside of the list.</p>
    </body>
